text: Vitória do Jari (), (Jari's Victory) is a municipality located in the southernmost tip of the state of Amapá in Brazil. Its population is 14,680 and its area is . Vitória do Jari has a population density of 5.9 inhabitants per square kilometer. The municipality contains 17% of the Rio Cajari Extractive Reserve, created in 1990. ==References== Category:Municipalities in Amapá Category:Populated places established in 1994 Category:1994 establishments in Brazil
